node.text:
This week on Think Loud Crew, the girls talk all about The List A.K.A the list of things that they desire in a partner, as well as dealbreakers! Don't have B.O. but please have a career. Don't live with your parents, but be a family man. Have to be good in bed and a good listener. Have to be emotionally available or don't come near me... It's good to have standards, but lists evolve, you might surprise yourself!

Follow us: 
Think Loud Crew IG: @thinkloudcrew
Cheyenne's IG: @cheynotshy
Shanan's IG: @hairbyshananc
R's IG: @rkylelynn

More about the show: 

Check out our YouTube channel: https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCEWHZqlWjGI1ZD9TwHBT8jg.

Don’t forget to subscribe to the podcast for free wherever you're listening or using this link: http://bit.ly/ThinkLoudCrewPodcast

node.title: The List: Emotionally available or don’t come near me

node.text:
This week on Think Loud Crew, the girls talk all about their postpartum experiences, postpartum depression, what they did to prepare, everything that went wrong, and how they learned from those experiences. They also share some tips on postpartum care such as a belly binding session, and having a postpartum recovery box!

Don't forget to do your kegels girls!

Find your Belly Binding sessions: https://bellibind.com/about

Follow us: 
Think Loud Crew IG: @thinkloudcrew
Cheyenne's IG: @cheynotshy
Shanan's IG: @hairbyshananc
R's IG: @rkylelynn

More about the show: 

Continue watching on YouTube: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=UoU0CdE1LrI.

It's Q&A time in this episode of Think Loud Crew! The girls answer questions about cheating, weed, mom guilt, Cheyenne's relationship with Taylor, how to co-parent, if they planned their kids, and how to deal with a disrespectful baby daddy/baby momma!

Tune in to hear all about it. It's time to get real!

Follow us:

node.text:
Cheyenne, R, and Shanan are back again, and this time they've invited their favorite Teen Mom OG producer, JC Cueva, to talk about his experience of being a traveling producer while still being a full time dad. He gives tips and tricks on how to spend quality time with his kids, even if it's virtually, and talks about what he's learned while being a producer at Teen Mom OG!

Follow JC on IG: @j.c.cueva

Follow us:

node.text:
In this exciting new episode of Think Loud Crew, Cheyenne isn't pregnant anymore!! Ace finally came into this world, and Chey tells all about her 2nd experience giving birth: from her pre-labor contractions, to finally pulling the baby straight out of her!

Birthing a child isn't glamorous, especially if your future father-in-law is present during the birth. Stay tuned to hear all about it!

Follow us: 
Think Loud Crew IG: @thinkloudcrew
Cheyenne's IG: @cheynotshy
Shanan's IG: @hairbyshananc
R's IG: @rkylelynn

More about the show: 
Check out our YouTube channel: https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCEWHZqlWjGI1ZD9TwHBT8jg.

Don’t forget to subscribe to the podcast for free wherever you're listening or using this link: http://bit.ly/ThinkLoudCrewPodcast

node.text:
Today marks the beginning of World Breastfeeding Week 🖤 
This week is about normalizing breastfeeding, raising awareness, & improving support for breastfeeding parents. It focuses on educating, encouraging and empowering those who are on their breastfeeding journey.

Breastfeeding can look different for everyone. After nursing Ryder for 2 years, I am determined to do the same with Ace. My current journey has been a lot harder, mentally & physically. The first few weeks were extremely tough. As he would latch, I would be dreading the pain that would follow. My nipples cracked, bled, peeled, & I swear they were mad at me. I was confused because they didn’t do this with my first experience breastfeeding & I was ashamed that it didn’t come as easy this time. Breastfeeding is not easy, mothers need support, & to know they aren’t alone. 

I am now exclusively breastfeeding Ace and we truly have our good days and bad days but overall I am committed to nursing as long as my body permits it. 

What is your breastfeeding journey? 🖤 

Not every breastfeeding journey looks the same. No path is better than the other. I believe every feed should be celebrated. 
#supportisbest

(This photo was taken at Ace newborn shoot, my nipples were finally staring to heal and nursing wasn’t so tender. I wanted a picture to look back on an celebrate that I fought through the pain. Thank you @patty.othon for capturing my journey)
